Mark E. Ripple, born August 30, 1967 was an American money manager, expert horse racing handicapper,. and author of Handicapping the Wall Street Way. He was frequently sought after to pen articles, having written for American Turf Monthly, The Horse Jockey, CBS, and Southern Gaming Magazine. He has been featured in American Turf Monthly and Motley Fool, and has been a featured financial commentator for CBS Market Watch. Mark has given lectures at numerous colleges including the University of Pennsylvania, Hudson Valley Community College, and Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute.
